llm_res.rule: The contract must implement the `balanceOf` function as specified in the ERC721 standard.
When transferring to a contract, the contract must implement `ERC721TokenReceiver` and return the correct magic value.
Returns the symbol of the token. E.g. "HIX". OPTIONAL - This method can be used to improve usability, but interfaces and other contracts MUST NOT expect these values to be present.
